      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''Heaping Helpings of Nostalgia, a Child's Plate of Profit'' (July 2) included a suggestion that America's roadside diners need to attract a younger crowd.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''Heaping Helpings of Nostalgia, a Child's Plate of Profit'' (July 2) included a suggestion that America's roadside diners need to attract a younger crowd.</p>
        <p>One obvious solution would be for all diner owners to ban smoking. Health-sensible restaurants attract younger people by being nonsmoking only.</p>
        <p>WILLIAM J. PARENTE  Scranton, Pa., July 3</p>
      </block>
